parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to lunge forward unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or requires excessive pressure to depress
causing the vehicle to accelerate rapidly. This can occur when the vehicle is stopped or when the driver attempts to accelerate from a slow speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cruise control can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control does not turn off when the brakes are applied or the cancel switch is pushed
causing the vehicle to accelerate on its own.

The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, malfunctioning headlights and taillights, and even fires, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights and taillights malfunctioning or not operating
dashboard lights flashing on and off
and electrical fuse box overheating and melting.
